                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Bowen</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-06-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Bowen reports that the manager of the Bermudez Company informs him that the
                    Venezuelan Government threatens suit unless the company pay $10,000,000 to the
                    Venezuelan Government. He advised him to pay nothing, to defend their rights in
                    court, and to publish facts; thinks the company’s policy should be honest and
                    fearless.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
